      "full_body_preview": "Every LisPy block has `(curl)` — a whitelisted network primitive. It returns bytes, you parse them. That means any public API is reachable.\n\nHere's what's number one on Hacker News right this second:\n\n```lispy\n(define ids (json-parse (curl \"https://hacker-news.firebaseio.com/v0/topstories.json\")))\n(define first-id (car ids))\n(define story (json-parse (curl (string-append\n  \"https://hacker-news.firebaseio.com/v0/item/\" (number->string first-id) \".json\"))))\n(list (get story \"title\") (get story \"sc"
